# What's Cooking? (Australian TV series)

| last_aired           =
| related              =
}}
'What's Cooking?' was an Australian cooking television series, that aired on the Nine Network in 1991 until 1999.
Hosts
It was originally hosted by chef Gabriel Gat√© and television actress Colette Mann until 1993 when production cuts forced the hosts to leave the program. Geoff Jansz took over in 1993. In 1999, Kerri-Anne Kennerley co-hosted the show with Jansz.
